description: Borrowed from Latin circumnāvigātus, perfect passive participle of circumnāvigō (“sail round something, circumnavigate”), from circum (“about, around”) + nāvigō (“sail, navigate”), from nāvis (“ship”) + agō (“do”). Surface analysis: circum- +‎ navigate.

verbs.description: circumnavigate (third-person singular simple present circumnavigates, present participle circumnavigating, simple past and past participle circumnavigated)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To travel completely around somewhere or something, especially by sail.
examples: Synonyms: compass, (obsolete) environ, go around, sail around

entries.meaning: (intransitive, sailing) To sail around the world.
